title: Goldman Sachs Stock Sputters Despite Brisk Run of Business
sub_head: While deal making and trading exceed expectations, the firmâ€™s shares are lagging behind those of some top rivals
body:
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. has delivered on its financial promises. Investors remain unimpressed.
When the bank updated its corporate strategy in a January 2020 presentation to investors, it set new goals for how profitably it uses shareholder money. Goldman said it would target a return on equity of 13% to 14% within the next several years.
